There are currently two methods to install k3match.
To install the C library only use "cmake", to install the Python module use "distutils".

1. CMAKE

1.1 PREREQUISITES

    In addition to the C standard library and a C compiler
    you need the following packages.

    cmake (>= 2.8.0)

1.2 INSTALLING

    mkdir build
    cd build
    cmake ../
    make
    sudo make install

2. DISTUTILS

2.1 PREREQUISITES

    In addition to the C standard library and a C compiler
    you need the following packages.

    python (>= 2.6.0)
    python-dev (>= 2.6.0)
    python-numpy (>= 1.4.0)
    python-numpy-dev (>= 1.4.0)

2.2 INSTALLING

    sudo python setup.py install

